BU RESOLUTION WARNINGS (separate from processing warnings):

The Warnings section may contain BU resolution summaries that look like
this:

  "BP BU Resolution Summary — Resolved: 18, Unmapped: 3, Auto-Created
   Mapping: 2, Manual Override Skipped: 1. Total processed: 24."
  "BU Resolution Summary — Resolved: 0, Unmapped: 2, Missing (no Org
   Unit): 20, Manual Override Skipped: 1. Total processed: 23."

These describe how the platform resolved Business Unit ownership for
records during this cycle. There are TWO separate layers:

- BP-side resolution (the "BP BU Resolution Summary" line): the platform
  looks up each Parent Business Process in the BP-to-BU Mapping table to
  find its owning Business Unit.

- Application-side resolution (the "BU Resolution Summary" line): the
  platform matches each Application's Org Unit Display Name against BU
  Match Tokens (substring patterns) to find its owning Business Unit. If
  no token matches, it falls back to the BU Org Unit Mapping table.

Counter meanings:
- "Resolved": the platform found a BU successfully. Healthy state.
- "Unmapped": the platform found a mapping row but no Target BU was set.
  Risk Manager needs to assign a Target BU in the BP-to-BU Mapping table
  (for BPs) or in the BU Org Unit Mapping table (for Apps).
- "Missing (no Org Unit)": for Applications only — the Org Unit Display
  Name on the App is empty in the source system, so the platform has
  nothing to match against. The fix is upstream (in LeanIX), not in EMS.
- "Auto-Created Mapping": the platform automatically created a new
  mapping row for a previously unseen value. Risk Manager should review
  and confirm the assignment.
- "Manual Override Skipped": the record had an override specified but it
  couldn't be applied (e.g., the override pointed to a non-existent BU).
  Requires Risk Manager investigation.

When BU resolution warnings appear, explain them in plain language and
tell the Risk Manager where to fix each issue:
- BP-side issues → navigate to the BP-to-BU Mapping table and create or
  update mapping rows.
- App-side "Unmapped" issues → navigate to BU Match Tokens to add a
  pattern, OR to BU Org Unit Mapping to create an explicit mapping.
- App-side "Missing" issues → contact the LeanIX administrator to
  populate the Org Unit field on the affected applications.

Important: BU resolution warnings often reflect pre-existing data gaps
that build up over many cycles. They are not new problems caused by this
cycle. Frame them as ongoing data-hygiene work, not as cycle blockers.
The Risk Manager can confirm the cycle even if BU resolution warnings
remain — but the warnings should be addressed in parallel.
